South Western Districts Cricket on Thursday, 18 July, showed their support for Mandela Day when they handed out soup and bread to patients at the Emergency Ward of the Oudtshoorn Hospital. More than 300 patients were fed. <img class="alignnone wp-image-27040 size-full" src="https://diehoorn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/12-MANDELA-DAY-2019-3.jpg" alt="" width="850" height="637" srcset="https://diehoorn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/12-MANDELA-DAY-2019-3.jpg 850w, https://diehoorn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/12-MANDELA-DAY-2019-3-300x225.jpg 300w, https://diehoorn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/12-MANDELA-DAY-2019-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://diehoorn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/12-MANDELA-DAY-2019-3-672x504.jpg 672w, https://diehoorn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/12-MANDELA-DAY-2019-3-360x270.jpg 360w, https://diehoorn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/12-MANDELA-DAY-2019-3-480x360.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" />